# Word audio playback

## Prefer helpers — do not invent new players

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Course word / option (`audio` + TTS fallback) | `playCourseAudio(audioUrl, ttsText, audioRef, stopPrior)` |
| Game question stem (`audioUrl` or full/blank sentence TTS) | `playGameQuestionStem(q, audioRef, stopPrior, options?)` |
| Resolve / warm cached MP3 | `resolveAudioSrc(url)` / `prefetchAudioUrls(urls)` |
| Match unit word audio inside a sentence | `findWordAudioInSentence(text, words)` |
| Book vocab / dictionary (TTS only, no MP3) | `speak(text, rate)` from `utils.ts` |

Never call `new Audio(url)` or `fetch(audioUrl)` directly in hooks/components — always go through `resolveAudioSrc` so Cache API + in-memory blob URLs stay shared.

## Cache layers (`audioUrlCache.ts`)

1. **In-memory** `Map` — original URL → `blob:` object URL (instant replay)
2. **In-flight dedupe** — parallel callers share one Promise per URL
3. **Cache API** (`kidstory-audio-v1`) — persists blobs across sessions
4. **Fallback** — on fetch/cache failure, return the original URL so playback can still try

```ts
const src = await resolveAudioSrc("/sounds/banana.mp3");
const el = new Audio(src);
await el.play();
```

Warm ahead of need: `prefetchAudioUrls(words.map((w) => w.audio).filter(Boolean))`.

## Session hook pattern

```tsx
const audioRef = useRef<HTMLAudioElement | null>(null);

const stopAudio = useCallback(() => {
  const a = audioRef.current;
  if (a) {
    a.pause();
    a.currentTime = 0;
  }
  window.speechSynthesis?.cancel();
}, []);

useEffect(() => () => stopAudio(), [stopAudio]);

const playWord = useCallback(() => {
  if (!word) return;
  void playCourseAudio(word.audio, word.word, audioRef, stopAudio);
}, [word, stopAudio]);
```

- Always `stopPrior` before starting new audio (MP3 or TTS)
- Fire-and-forget with `void playCourseAudio(...)` from click/effects
- Cleanup on unmount via `stopAudio`
- After `speechSynthesis.cancel()`, defer TTS with `queueMicrotask` (already inside `playCourseAudio`) — Chromium often drops same-turn `speak()`

## Data

- Course words: optional `audio: "/sounds/<word>.mp3"` under `public/sounds/`
- Spell/MC questions: optional `audioUrl` (same path style)
- Prefer MP3 when the file exists; TTS (`rate ≈ 0.92`) is the automatic fallback

## Don't

- Duplicate Cache API / blob URL logic outside `audioUrlCache.ts`
- Skip `stopAudio` when advancing cards/questions (overlapping speech)
- Use `speak()` for course practice when `word.audio` may exist — use `playCourseAudio`
